==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[Suède]]'' Sweden, swedish

===Noun===
'''suede''' (''uncountable'')
# A type of soft [[leather]], made from [[calfskin]], with a [[brushed]] [[texture]] to resemble [[fabric]]. It is often used to make [[boot]]s, [[clothing]] and [[fashion]] accessories.

